Job Description Research Scientist in Data Mining

Job Type: Full-time

Location: Cambridge, UK

We are looking for research scientists working on data mining and related areas, including natural language processing, information retrieval and recommender systems, to join JD AI. Candidates with both theoretical and applied interests are encouraged to apply.

JD offers endless data-rich application scenarios, including e-commence, supply-chain, logistics, big data, cloud computing, IoT, marketing, finance and robotics, to drive our research on data mining. We have open publication policy and researchers at JD AI have a strong record of publication in top platforms, such as ICML, NIPS, AAAI, IJCAI, KDD, ICDM, WSDM, SIGIR, CIKM, WWW, ACL, EMNLP, CVPR, and ICCV.

Responsibilities:
Conduct data-driven research, challenge the state of the art in data mining and its relevant areas, and publish research work in top research platforms, such as KDD, SIGIR, WWW, and ACL;
Innovate and develop new ideas for applied AI in JD products and services;
Work with business, engineering and product teams to form an understanding of the emerging technical requirements and identify/establish/participate in novel research programs to address identified technical challenges.
Basic Qualifications:
PhD in data mining, information retrieval or natural language processing;
Track-record in developing novel techniques and approaches, e.g., publications in one or more of the following: KDD, ICDM, WSDM, SIGIR, CIKM, WWW, ACL, EMNLP, etc.
Solid background in statistical approaches or other emerging methods for modelling data (structured, unstructured or linked);
Strong programming skills in at least one object-oriented programming language (Python, C++, Java, Scala, etc.)
Experience in DM/IR/NLP algorithm implementation, as well as the ability to improve/modify standard algorithms (e.g. change the optimization objective, work out an alternative mathematical model and implement it);
Ability to develop prototypes by manipulating and analysing complex, high-volume, high-dimensionality data from varying sources;
Eager to learn new algorithms, new application areas and new tools;
Excellent written and oral communication skills.
Preferred Qualifications
Deep academic or industrial expertise (post PhD 5+ years) in one or more related areas;
An active contributor to the relevant international research communities;
Hands-on experience with big data platforms such as Hadoop and Spark;
Previous experience in managing a dedicated research team;
Knowledge of, or experience in, building and deploying production-quality large-scale applications related to data mining, information retrieval or natural language processing.

Job Description Machine Learning Scientist

Job Type: Full-time

Location: Cambridge, UK

Department: JD.com Artificial Intelligence Department

Your application will be available until September 3rd, 2018.

JD AI focuses on the continuous innovation and optimization of algorithms to meet our developing business needs. Significant areas of research include natural language processing, machine learning, including deep learning and reinforcement learning, and computer vision. We maintain AI labs in Beijing and Silicon Valley.

We are looking for machine learning research scientists to join JD AI . Candidates with both theoretical and applied interests are encouraged to apply. We are interested in a wide range of machine learning, knowledge representation, and reasoning problems, with a focus on reinforced intelligent agents that can make "clever" actions by naturally interacting with the physical world. They could work alone in single-agent learning systems or jointly in multi-agent, distributed learning systems. The subject areas include, but are not limited to:
Reinforcement learning
Deep learning and adversarial machine learning
Knowledge representation and (symbolic) reasoning
Control theory
Operational research
Optimisation
Robotics
Multiagent systems
Algorithmic game theory and mechanism design
Dialogue systems
We encourage both theoretical and applied research work, and JD.com offers endless practical scenarios, including e-commence, supply-chain, logistics, big data, cloud computing, IoT, marketing, finance and robotics, to inspire research. We have an open publication policy, and researchers at JD AI have strong record of publication in top AI research venues including ICML, NIPS, AAAI, IJCAI, KDD, ICDM, WSDM, SIGIR, CIKM, WWW, ACL, EMNLP, CVPR, and ICCV.

Responsibilities:
Conduct cutting-edge research on machine learning, challenge the state of the art, actively participate in the research community, and publish research work in top research platforms such as ICML, NIPS, AAAI, IJCAI;
Work with business, engineering and product teams to form an understanding of the emerging technical requirements, and identify/establish/participate in novel research programs to address identified technical challenges;
Define and drive a technical vision and strategies to integrate novel machine learning algorithms into the existing production systems and business decision making processes.
Basic Qualifications:
PhD in machine learning or related field, with research published in to platforms, such as ICML, NIPS, AAAI, IJCAI or their equivalent;
Solid background in statistical approaches or other latest approaches and methodologies in AI;
Strong programming skills in at least one object-oriented programming language (Python, C++, Java, Scala, etc.);
Experience in machine learning algorithm implementation, as well as the ability to make use of open source tools to further develop models;
Experience with a deep learning framework, such as TensorFlow or PyTorch;
Ability to develop prototypes by manipulating and analysing complex, high-volume, high-dimensional data from varying sources;
Eager to learn new algorithms, new application areas and new tools;
Ability to communicate and collaborate with other researchers and engineers, including our team members in China (ability to speak Chinese is required), excellent written and oral communication skill.
Preferred Qualifications
Deep academic or industry expertise (post PhD 5+ years) in one or more related areas;
An active contributor to the relevant international research communities, and able to create and act as a champion of a specific sub-topic and particular technology or application;
Hands-on experience in applying machine learning techniques to solve real-world problems;
Previous experience in managing a dedicated research team;
Knowledge of, or experience in, building and deploying production-quality large-scale applications related to machine learning.
Ability to communicate and collaborate with other researchers and engineers, including our team members in China (ability to speak Chinese is required), excellent written and oral communication skill.

Job Description - Research Scientists in Robotics

Job Type: Full-time

Location: Cambridge, UK

We are looking for research scientists in robotics to join JD AI JD.com possesses a large body of novel applications related to robotics, including social home robots, automatic guided vehicles for warehouses, and autonomous cars or unmanned aerial vehicles for delivery. The skills, qualifications, and experience required to perform the role are a first degree in a relevant discipline and a PhD degree (or about to be awarded a PhD degree) in automatic control, mechanical engineering, electrical engineering, computer science, or other related areas. Besides encouraging the investigation on new applications, JD.com also has an open policy in publication. Our researchers have strong publication records in top robotic conferences and journals, which include NIPS, ICML, AAAI, TAROS, Humanoids, RoboSoft, ICRA, IEEE Transactions on Robotics.

Responsibilities
Design and develop state-of-the-art applications on robotics; publish research work at robotics conferences and journals, such as TAROS, Humanoids, RoboSoft, ICRA, IEEE Transactions on Robotics, or general AI conferences such as ICML, NIPS, AAAI etc.;
Work together with our machine learning, computer vision, and other teams for larger integrated projects;
Prototype hardware or software solutions for robotic applications;
Work closely with the engineering team to integrate solutions into robots or other platforms;
Basic Qualifications
PhD in Automatic Control, Computer Science, Electrical Engineering, Mechanical Engineering or equivalent with a focus on robotics;
Publication records on robotics in preferred journals and conferences, such as TAROS and IEEE Transactions on Robotics;
Research experience in one or more areas of robotics, such as biologically inspired robotics, soft robotics, modelling and simulation of biological systems, soft matter modelling and analysis;
Knowledge in programming language or electronic circuits;
Ability to plan and manage time, tasks, milestones and resources to meet project objectives.
Preferred Qualifications
Academic or industrial expertise (post PhD >5 years) in one or more related areas;
An active contributor to the relevant international research communities;
Experience in building and leading a technical team.

Job Description - Research Scientists in Spoken Language Processing
Job Type: Full-time
Location: Cambridge, UK
We are looking for research scientists in spoken language processing to join JD AI JD.com to innovate a large body of novel applications related to speech processing and natural language understanding, ranging from e-commerce voice search, automatic helpline service, to intelligent audio box, to name just a few. Candidates with broad interests in speech and language studies are encouraged to apply. JD.com also has an open policy in publication in promoting the state-of-the-art research work. Our researchers have strong publication records in top AI conferences, which include speech and language conferences such as ICASSP, Interspeech, ASRU, ACL, NAACL.
Responsibilities
Design and develop state-of-the-art applications on speech recognition/synthesis, speaker recognition, spoken dialogue system, spoken language translation, and emotion recognition; publish research work at speech and language conferences, such as ICASSP, Interspeech, ASRU, SLT, ACL, EMNLP, COLING;
Work together with our machine learning, computer vision, and other teams for larger integrated projects;
Prototype hardware or software solutions for speech and language applications;
Work closely with the engineering team to integrate solutions into autonomous robotics or other platforms.
Basic Qualifications
PhD in Computer Science, Electrical Engineering or equivalent with a focus on speech and language processing;
Publication records on speech and language processing at referred conferences and in journals such as ICASSP, ACL, TASLP, CL, or machine learning related such as ICML, NIPS, AAAI;
Research experience in one or more areas of speech and language processing, such as speech enhancement, speech recognition, speech synthesis, speaker recognition, spoken dialogue systems, and spoken language translation;
Experience with the speech toolkits such as HTK or Kaldi, or general deep learning frameworks such as TensorFlow or PyTorch;
Ability to plan and manage time, tasks, milestones and resources to meet project objectives;
Preferred Qualifications
Academic or industrial expertise (post PhD >5 years) in one or more related areas;
An active contributor to the relevant international research communities;
Experience in building and leading a technical team;

